FBIS4-55179 "dreeu091_s_94002" FBIS-EEU-94-091 Daily Report 29 Apr 1994 SLOVENIA Statistic Institute Reports Apr Inflation Statistic Institute Reports Apr Inflation AU1005173294 Ljubljana SLOVENEC in Slovene 29 Apr 94 p 1 AU1005173294 Ljubljana SLOVENEC Slovene BFN ["D.H."-initialed report: "April Inflation 2.1 Percent"] [Text] Ljubljana -- According to a report by the Slovene Statistical Institute, retail prices in April have increased by 2.1 percent, therefore, this is how high the April inflation is. In the month just ending, the prices of vital necessities increased by 2.4 percent. In the first four months of this year, retail prices increased by 6.1 percent and the prices of vital necessities by 7.2 percent. In one year, retail prices increased by 20.8 percent and the cost of living by 21.8 percent.
